64. The pronoun is, ea, id, agrees in gender with its antecedent, that is with the noun to which it refers.

Rem. 39. Hence if is, eum, eo, ete.. refer to things masculine, and if ea, eam, etc.. refer to things feminine, they are translated by it, not by Ite, him, her, etc.
